        "@id": "https://ww3.ticketpro.ca/event.php?event_id=10906"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "Green Room Session with Scott Cleveland"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>Join us for an intimate evening with acclaimed pianist, singer, and composer Scott Cleveland as part of our Green Room Session series.</p>\n<p>A graduate of the prestigious Berklee College of Music, Scott is a versatile cross-genre artist whose music blends elements of jazz, classical, folk, and contemporary songwriting into a distinctive and engaging sound. He also holds a Master of Music degree in Theory and Composition from University of Massachusetts Lowell and has been on the Jazz Faculty at the University of Maine for the past six years. </p>\n<p>Throughout his career, Scott has released six independent albums, showcasing his talents as a performer, composer, and storyteller. His catalog spans both digital and physical formats, with three albums available on Bandcamp and three released on vinyl and cassette.</p>\n<p>Known for his expressive piano playing, thoughtful compositions, and warm stage presence, Scott creates performances that are both musically adventurous and deeply personal. This special Green Room Session offers audiences a rare opportunity to experience his artistry up close in an intimate listening-room setting.</p>\n<p>Don't miss an evening of original music, captivating stories, and exceptional musicianship with Scott Cleveland.\n</p>\n\n\n\n<style>\n.location-page-temp {display: block!important;}\n</style>\n\n"
      }
